Bring a #pot of water to the boil over a high heat. When the water is boiling, add
the @egg noodle nests{3} to the pot, remove from the heat and leave for ~{3%mins}.
After 3 mins, drain the noodles into a #colander and then run under cold water to
stop them cooking anymore.

Remove the core from the @green pepper{2}(thinly sliced) and thinly slice. Cut the
@red onion{1} in half through the root, peel and then slice into half moon shapes.

Chop the top and bottom off the @carrot{1}(peeled and made into ribbons using a
peeler), peel and then use your #peeler to make carrot ribbons. Run the peeler
from the very top of the carrot to the bottom. Repeat until all of the carrot is
used up. Pop the carrot ribbons into a #bowl and keep to one side for later.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}. Peel and grate the @ginger{1} and then
thinly slice the @red chilli{1}. Heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add a
splash of @oil{} and when the oil is hot add the @pork medallion{4} to the pan.
Cook for ~{8%mins} on each side, turning halfway through. You want the pork to be
golden brown on both sides.

> Tip: The pork is cooked when the centre is no longer pink.

As the pork steaks cook, heat another #frying pan{} or #wok over a high heat and
add a splash of @oil{}. Add your pepper and cook for ~{5%mins}. Move them around
every minute or so to ensure even cooking. After 5 mins add your onion and cook
for another ~{2%mins}. Next add your garlic and ginger and cook for another
~{1%minute}.

Pour in the @soy sauce{1.5%tbsp}, a third of the @hoisin sauce{3%tbsp} and
@water{50%ml}. Heat until the sauce bubbles, then stir in your noodles. Reduce
the heat to low and cook for another ~{3%mins} until your noodles are piping hot.

When your pork is cooked, remove the pan from the heat, drain off any excess oil
and stir in the rest of your hoisin sauce. Roll your pork around in the hoisin
sauce. Squeeze the @lime{1}(juiced) juice onto your carrot ribbons and get ready
to plate.

Serve a generous amount of your noodles on a #plate and top with some carrot
ribbons. Slice each pork steak into six slices and pop on top of your noodles
and carrots. Spoon over your hoisin sauce from the pan. Finish with the crunchy
@beansprouts{100} and if you like it, a few slices of chilli.